<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FFCBCE1AFCD5F9A5DB9B3D2F" lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFFCBCE1BFCD5F9A5DE7D3B64" blockId="70.[810,1452,1652,2093]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFCD5F9A5D8F73AA0" bold="true" box="[810,932,1652,1678]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species in the group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFAEBF9A4DE263AA0" box="[1300,1397,1653,1678]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nattereri">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFAEBF9A4DE263AA0" box="[1300,1397,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">nattereri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are recognized by the following combination of characters: Medium to large in total length; embolus with three keels; BTA developed; serrated area above PAc in prolateral view reduced. Females are recognized by the spermathecae with two receptacles, without lateral swelling.
</paragraph>
